article.headline: Towson 73, William & Mary 60
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Gary Neal scored 26 points and Towson held off William and Mary's second-half surge to win 73-60 Tuesday night. Neal scored 15 of his points in the first-half when the Tigers (5-3, 1-0 Colonial Athletic Association) closed with an 18-4 run to open a 42-25 lead at the break. William and Mary's Nathan Mann made the game's first basket with a jumper, but Neal came back with a 3-pointer, and Towson didn't trail for the rest of the game. The Tribe (3-4, 0-1) outscored Towson 15-4 over about five minutes and pulled as close as six, the last 53-47 with 10:47 left, but they got no closer. Dennard Abraham scored 15 for Towson and Rocky Coleman had 10. Neal also had seven assists, and made four 3-pointers. David Schneider scored 18, Adam Payton 16 and Kyle Carrabine 10 for the Tribe. William and Mary shot just 35.2 percent.
